\subsection{Telegraph--advection core with admissible sources}
Extend the telegraph-stable core (Chapter~6) by a local advection drift
$\mathbf u(\mathbf x,t)$:
\begin{equation}
\tau\,\partial_t^2\Psi+\partial_t\Psi - c^2\nabla^2\Psi
\;+\; \mathbf u(\mathbf x,t)\!\cdot\!\nabla\Psi
\;=\; -\alpha_1\Psi-\alpha_3|\Psi|^2\Psi
\;+\; \nabla\!\cdot\!\big(D(\Psi)\nabla\Psi\big)
\;+\; \xi(\mathbf x,t).
\label{eq:plasma_tele_adv}
\end{equation}
Here $c,\tau>0$; $\alpha_1,\alpha_3\ge0$ are restorative/saturating gains;
$D(\Psi)\ge0$ is a local diffusion modulus; and $\xi$ is causal, zero-mean,
local noise (Chapter~11). The drift $\mathbf u$ is prescribed or obtained from a
separate local rule (e.g., a filtered background flow) subject to boundedness.

\paragraph{Local admissibility.}
Assume $\mathbf u\in L^\infty$ and Lipschitz on bounded sets, with
$\|\mathbf u\|_\infty\le u_{\max}=O(1)$; $D(\Psi)\in[0,D_{\max}]$, smooth;
$\alpha_3>0$ when parametric drives are present.

\subsection{Energy--coherence and advection balance}
Define the coherence density with a drift contribution handled by
skew-symmetric work:
\[
\mathcal E_{\text{coh}}(\Psi)=\tfrac12|\partial_t\Psi|^2+\tfrac{c^2}{2}|\nabla\Psi|^2
+\tfrac{\alpha_1}{2}|\Psi|^2+\tfrac{\alpha_3}{4}|\Psi|^4,
\quad E_{\text{coh}}(t)=\int_\Omega \mathcal E_{\text{coh}}\,d\mathbf x .
\]
Multiplying \eqref{eq:plasma_tele_adv} by $\partial_t\Psi$ and integrating over
$\Omega$ with periodic or appropriate boundary conditions yields
\[
\dot E_{\text{coh}}(t)
= -\int_\Omega \big(\tau\,|\partial_t^2\Psi|^2+|\partial_t\Psi|^2\big)\,dx
-\int_\Omega \nabla\partial_t\Psi\cdot D(\Psi)\nabla\Psi\,dx
+ \underbrace{\int_\Omega \partial_t\Psi\,(\mathbf u\!\cdot\!\nabla\Psi)\,dx}_{\text{skew (transport)}} 
+ \int_\Omega \partial_t\Psi\,\xi\,dx .
\]
Under periodic/Neumann boundaries, the advection term is skew and integrates to
a boundary flux; thus it does not create energy. With $D(\Psi)\ge0$ the flux is
dissipative. Hence the Energy--Coherence budget (Chapter~10) persists.

