\end{tabular}
\end{center}

Under \eqref{eq:group_xfer}--\eqref{eq:weights}, these ingredients match
one-to-one after unit rescaling and gain renormalization.

\subsection{Renormalization-style tuning (local recipe)}
Given a reference configuration $\mathcal P=(\tau,c,\alpha_1,\alpha_3,\beta_{\mathrm{pm}})$
and a target configuration $\mathcal P'$ with the same invariants \eqref{eq:invariants}:
\begin{enumerate}
\item Pick $\lambda=\dfrac{c'}{c}$ (space/time speed ratio).
\item Set $\tau'=\lambda^{-1}\tau$ and keep $\alpha_1'=\alpha_1$, $\alpha_3'=\alpha_3$.
\item Scale active drive $\beta_{\mathrm{pm}}'=\big(\tfrac{c'}{c}\big)^{2}\beta_{\mathrm{pm}}$
to keep $\beta_{\mathrm{pm}}/c^2$ invariant.
\item Keep $A$, $\widetilde W$, $\widetilde\Lambda$ unchanged; tune $(W_0',\lambda_0')$
by discrepancy and decay-rate targets (Ch.~10).
\end{enumerate}
This preserves dispersion, Lyapunov monotonicity, and residual consistency.

\subsection{Falsifiable transfer tests}
\begin{enumerate}
\item \textbf{Dispersion preservation:} compare $s_\pm(k)$ and $s'_\pm(k)$ via
the scaling rule $s'_\pm(k)=\lambda\,s_\pm(\lambda^{-1}k)$; require matching
real parts (stability) and scaled imaginary parts (oscillation).
\item \textbf{Energy budget:} verify $E_{\text{coh}}'(t)$ is nonincreasing modulo
source work, mirroring $E_{\text{coh}}(t)$ after rescaling time by $\lambda$.
\item \textbf{Residual statistics:} show that the whitened residual norm
$\|W^{1/2}(G\varepsilon-\delta)\|_2$ has the same distribution before/after transfer,
up to the scalar anchors $(W_0,\lambda_0)$.
\item \textbf{Locking behavior:} when applicable, demonstrate that peak values
and settling times of $(\rho_{\mathrm{lock}},\chi_{\mathrm{lock}})$ scale by
the predicted factor $\lambda$.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{What does \emph{not} transfer (guardrails)}
The cross-domain map is \emph{local-only}. Nonlocal couplings, global constraints,
or history-dependent kernels (ruled out by the governance) are \emph{not}
transported by \eqref{eq:group_xfer}. Any empirical improvement from such terms
must be treated as a separate, explicitly declared model layer.

\paragraph{Takeaway.}
Similarity via \((\Pi,\Theta)\), combined with the rescaling
\eqref{eq:group_xfer} and the local source grammar, yields a portable and
falsifiable map between domains. It preserves the telegraph stability window,
Energy--Coherence budget, and residual-layer statistics while keeping the entire
construction dimensionless, K-free, and local-only.
